<h2>Goals</h2>
  <li>Utilize Apple's ARKit to place virtual content at tracked, real-world locations within my apartment.</li>
  <li>Measure and model my apartment with computer-aided design and augmented reality software.</li>
  <li>Create an iOS application that renders virtual wall studs to match the world space in my apartment.</li>
<h2>Takeaways</h2>
  <li>ARKit provides many useful functions to perform world tracking, surface detection and model placement.</li>
  <li><a href="https://www.magicplan.app/">Magicplan</a> uses augmented reality and computer vision effectively to model and export 3D spaces.</li>
  <li>In addition to world tracking, image tracking may be an effective approach to accurately render virtual wall studs.</li>
